SIMPLE: invalid
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invalid
<hw>In*val"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>valid</ets>: cf. F. <ets>invalide</ets>, L.
<ets>invalidus</ets> infirm, weak. Cf. <er>Invalid</er>
infirm.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of no force, weight, or cogency; not valid;
weak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Having no force, effect, or
efficacy; void; null; <as>as, an <ex>invalid</ex> contract or
agreement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invalid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Invalid
<hw>In"va*lid</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>invalide</ets>, <ets>n. & a.</ets>, L. <ets>invalidus</ets>,
<pos>a.</pos> See <er>Invalid</er> null.]</ety> <def>A person who is
weak and infirm; one who is disabled for active service; especially, one
in chronic ill health who is unable to care for himself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invalid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Invalid
<hw>In"va*lid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Invalid</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Not well; feeble; infirm;
sickly; <as>as, he had an <ex>invalid</ex> daughter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invalid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Invalid
<hw>In"va*lid</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make or render
invalid or infirm.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Invalided</xex>, bent, and almost
blind.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To classify or enroll as an invalid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Peace coming, he was <qex>invalided</qex> on half pay.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invalidate</ent>⟦br⟧
